{"lemma":"قُرْءاً","slug":"قُرْءاً","root":"ق.ر.#","root_slug":"ق-ر-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ر-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n35373","n35374","n35375"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%A1%D8%A7%D9%8B"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n35373","headword_ar":"قَرْءٌ","root":"qrA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quro'N","text_ar":"قُرْءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb, K,) or the latter is a simple subst. and the former is an inf. n., (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A menstruation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a state of purity from the menstrual discharge:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K, &c.:) thus having two contr. meanings: (S, O, K:) said by IAth to have the latter meaning accord. to Esh-Sháfi'ee and the people of El-Hijáz, and the former meaning accord. to Aboo-Haneefeh and the people of El-' Irák: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, S, Mgh, O, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAriy^N","text_ar":"قَارِيٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, O;) as in the sayings,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hab~ati Alr~iyHu liqaroy^ihaA","text_ar":"هَبَّتِ الرِّيحُ لِقَرْيِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liqaAriy^ihaA","text_ar":"لِقَارِيِهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wind blew at its time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kt, Mgh;) and this is the primary signification (IAth, Mgh, O) accord. to AA [and some others]; (Mgh;) whence [accord. to them] the first and second of the meanings mentioned above: (Kt, S, IAth, Mgh, O:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaro'N","text_ar":"قَرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"termination of a menstruation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and some say, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period between two menstruations:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) accord. to Zj, it means the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"collecting of the blood in the womb;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is only in the case of becoming pure from menstruation: (TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqoraA='N","text_ar":"اَقْرَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quruwo'N","text_ar":"قُرُوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqoruw^N","text_ar":"اَقْرُوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) the last of which [as also properly the first] is a pl. of pauc.; (S, O, Msb;) or when"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaro'N","text_ar":"قَرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quro'N","text_ar":"قُرْءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"has the first of the meanings assigned to it above the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqoraA='N","text_ar":"اَقْرَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and when it has the second thereof the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quruwo'N","text_ar":"قُرُوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) respecting the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"val`vapa quruwo'K","text_ar":"ثَلٰثَةَ قُرُوْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur [ii. 228], As says, it should by rule be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"val`vapa A^aqoruw^K","text_ar":"ثَلٰثَةَ اَقْرُوٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, TA:) the grammarians say that it is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"val`vapF mina Alquruwo'i","text_ar":"ثَلٰثَةً مِنَ القُرُوْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; thus in the L: (TA:) or they say that it is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"val`vapa A^aqoruw^K mina Alquruwo'i","text_ar":"ثَلٰثَةَ اَقْرُوٍ مِنَ القُرُوْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but some of them say that it is allowable to use a pl. of mult. in relation to three and more as far as ten [inclusively] without [the necessity of] rendering the phrase otherwise in grammatical analysis. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rhyme:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, K, TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqoraA='N","text_ar":"اَقْرَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, O, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quruwo'N","text_ar":"قُرُوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O) signifying the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rhymes"},{"kind":"text","text":"of verses; (Z, O, TA;) which terminate like as do the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AqrA='","text_ar":"اقرا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the states of purity from menstruation; (Z, TA;) [i. e., they are thus called] because they terminate, and limit, the verses: (O:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqoraA='u Al$~iEori","text_ar":"اَقْرَا=ءُ الشِّعْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"several modes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manners."},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"species,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, O, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"metres,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scopes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA,) of verse, or poetry: (IAth, O, K, TA:) the sing. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaro'N","text_ar":"قَرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quro'N","text_ar":"قُرْءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and some say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiro'N","text_ar":"قِرْءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qariYo","text_ar":"قَرِىْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qariY~N","text_ar":"قَرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and some say that it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qarowN","text_ar":"قَرْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qariY~N","text_ar":"قَرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [also]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqoriyapN","text_ar":"اَقْرِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.]. (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA Al$~iEoru EalaY qaro'i h`*aA Al$~iEori","text_ar":"هٰذَا الشِّعْرُ عَلَى قَرْءِ هٰذَا الشِّعْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This poetry is according to the mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of this poetry."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) See also 10, first sentence. ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A periodical festival;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiydN","text_ar":"عِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A fever"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an intermittent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a periodically-recurrent, fever"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAy^ibN","text_ar":"غَايِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing becoming absent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unapparent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"setting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"like a star: see 4]. (TA.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quro'u Alfarasi","text_ar":"قُرْءُ الفَرَسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The days of the mare's desiring the stallion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of her being covered:"},{"kind":"text","text":"one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiYa fiY qaroy^ihaA","text_ar":"هِىَ فِى قَرْيِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY A^aqoraAy^ihaA","text_ar":"فِى اَقْرَايِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She is in her days of desiring"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) See also 1, first quarter; and see 10, third sentence."}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","K","S","O","TA","IAth","Kt","Z"]},{"entry_id":"n35374","headword_ar":"قُرْءٌ","root":"qrA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph, in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n35375","headword_ar":"قِرْءٌ","root":"qrA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaro'N","text_ar":"قَرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last quarter: ―         -b2-  and see also the paragraph here following."},{"kind":"page_break","n":2504}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}